      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: OptionStatement
        children:
          - kind: OptionKeyword
            text: Option
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: ExplicitKeyword
            text: Explicit
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\r\n"
      - kind: OptionStatement
        children:
          - kind: OptionKeyword
            text: Option
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: PrivateKeyword
            text: Private
          - kind: Whitespace
            text: " "
          - kind: ModuleKeyword
            text: Module
          - kind: Newline
            text: "\r\n"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'*******************************************************************************"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'' Methods in this library module allow direct native memory manipulation in VBA"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'' regardless of:"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "''  - the host Application (Excel, Word, AutoCAD etc.)"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "''  - the operating system (Mac, Windows)"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "''  - application environment (x32, x64)"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'' A single API call to RtlMoveMemory API is needed to start the remote"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "''  referencing mechanism. Inside a REMOTE_MEMORY type, a 'remoteVT' Variant is"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "''  used to manipulate the VarType of the 'memValue' that we want to read/write."
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "''  The remote manipulation of the VarType is done by setting the VT_BYREF flag"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "''  on the 'remoteVT' Variant. This is done by using a CopyMemory API but only"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "''  once per initialization of the REMOTE_MEMORY variable (see MemIntAPI). Note"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "''  that besides the Static REMOTE_MEMORY used in MemIntAPI all the other memory"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "''  structs are initialized through InitRemoteMemory with no API calls. Once the"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "''  flag is set, the 'remoteVT' is used to change the VarType of the first"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "''  Variant just by using a native VBA assignment operation (needs a utility"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "''  method for correct redirection). In order for the 'memValue' Variant to"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "''  point to aspecific memory address, 2 steps are needed:"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "''   1) the required address is assigned to the 'memValue' Variant"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "''   2) the VarType of the 'memValue' Variant is remotely changed via the"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "''      'remoteVT' Variant (must be done ByRef in any utility method)"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'*******************************************************************************"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'Used for raising errors"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: DimStatement
