      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'Method purpose explanation at:"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'https://gist.github.com/cristianbuse/b9cc79164c1d31fdb30465f503ac36a9"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'Practical note Jan-2021 from Vladimir Vissoultchev (https://github.com/wqweto):"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'This is mostly not needed in client application code even for LARGEADDRESSAWARE"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'   32-bit processes nowadays as a reliable technique to prevent pointer"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'   arithmetic overflows is to VirtualAlloc a 64KB sentinel chunk around 2GB"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'   boundary at application start up so that the boundary is never (rarely)"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'   crossed in normal pointer operations."
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'This same sentinel chunk fixes native PropertyBag as well which has troubles"
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
      - kind: EndOfLineComment
        text: "'   when internal storage crosses 2GB boundary."
      - kind: Newline
        text: "\r\n"
