                  - kind: EndOfLineComment
                    text: "'*******************************************************************************"
                  - kind: Newline
                    text: "\r\n"
                  - kind: EndOfLineComment
                    text: "'Utility for 'MemCopy' - avoids extra stack frames"
                  - kind: Newline
                    text: "\r\n"
                  - kind: EndOfLineComment
                    text: "'The 'bytesCount' expected to be larger than 4 because the first 4 bytes are"
                  - kind: Newline
                    text: "\r\n"
                  - kind: EndOfLineComment
                    text: "'   needed for the destination BSTR's length."
                  - kind: Newline
                    text: "\r\n"
                  - kind: EndOfLineComment
                    text: "'The source can either be a String or an array of bytes depending on the first 4"
                  - kind: Newline
                    text: "\r\n"
                  - kind: EndOfLineComment
                    text: "'   bytes in the source. Choice between the 2 is based on speed considerations"
                  - kind: Newline
                    text: "\r\n"
                  - kind: EndOfLineComment
                    text: "'Note that no byte is changed in source regardless if BSTR or SAFEARRAY is used"
                  - kind: Newline
                    text: "\r\n"
                  - kind: EndOfLineComment
